statements.sql: select `users`.*, (select count(*) from `roles` inner join `user_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `user_roles`.`role_id` where `users`.`id` = `user_roles`.`user_id`) as `roles_count` from `users` where `email` = 'rakoto@gmail.com' or `username` = 'rakoto@gmail.com' limit 1

select `roles`.*, `user_roles`.`user_id` as `pivot_user_id`, `user_roles`.`role_id` as `pivot_role_id` from `roles` inner join `user_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `user_roles`.`role_id` where `user_roles`.`user_id` in (8)

select `fonctions`.*, (select count(*) from `users` inner join `personnel_fonctions` on `users`.`id` = `personnel_fonctions`.`personnel` where `fonctions`.`id` = `personnel_fonctions`.`fonction`) as `personnelles_count`, `personnel_fonctions`.`personnel` as `pivot_personnel`, `personnel_fonctions`.`fonction` as `pivot_fonction`, `personnel_fonctions`.`date_association` as `pivot_date_association ` from `fonctions` inner join `personnel_fonctions` on `fonctions`.`id` = `personnel_fonctions`.`fonction` where `personnel_fonctions`.`personnel` in (8)

select `roles`.*, `fonction_roles`.`fonction` as `pivot_fonction`, `fonction_roles`.`role` as `pivot_role` from `roles` inner join `fonction_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `fonction_roles`.`role` where `fonction_roles`.`fonction` in (2)
select `id` from `roles` inner join `fonction_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `fonction_roles`.`role` where `fonction_roles`.`fonction` = 2
